Question: Do you think standard tests accurately assess student abilities?
Answer:
my point of view is it depends what kind of ability the student are acquiring. if the student is trying to build up his knowledge base. the standard tests do help. you have a relible way to test to evaluate your understanding of the knowledge by taking the standard test. note those standard tests are developed by experts in that area. the test itself is high quality and also help students filter out corner knowledge, which made the learning process more productive. on the other hand, practical skills usually cant be  mastered by taking standard tests. for example, driving needs time to practice. passing the road test is just the beginning of being a experienced driver. it takes time to become confident and experienced to drive. 